# Project Brief

PortOS is a browser-based portfolio operating system built with Next.js, Zustand, Framer Motion, and Tailwind CSS.

## Vision

The project should feel like a real desktop operating system in the browser rather than a traditional website. The desktop itself is the primary interface. Information should live inside apps and windows, not as flat landing-page sections.

## Current Runtime

The current system includes:

- a desktop shell with wallpaper, menu bar, dock, icons, and floating windows
- a draggable AI teaser widget on the desktop shell that surfaces the agent before any app is opened
- a typed runtime store for apps, windows, and processes
- dynamic app loading from `src/apps/`
- window focus, minimize, maximize, drag, and resize behavior
- cross-app actions that let the AI agent launch apps, run guided flows, and prefill notes drafts

## App Philosophy

Applications must be isolated modules with real logic.

- no placeholder dashboards in the main app registry
- no dead buttons or non-functional controls
- each application may have its own local `theme.css`
- each application must keep behavior separate from system state

The most important product-facing app right now is the AI agent. It is not a generic chat feature - it is a portfolio attraction surface designed to represent Maivand, answer hiring/client questions, and guide people through the OS.

## Design Direction

The overall shell follows a macOS-inspired visual language, but apps are allowed to have their own distinct personalities as long as they stay usable and integrated with the OS.

The AI agent and desktop attraction surfaces should feel premium, minimal, and conversion-focused. They are part of the portfolio narrative, not utility-only controls.

## Technical Notes

- framework: Next.js App Router
- language: TypeScript / TSX
- state: Zustand
- motion: Framer Motion
- icons: Lucide
- styles: Tailwind CSS v4 + CSS variables

## Implemented Application Set

The current installed app set is:

- AI agent
- terminal
- docs
- blog
- contact
- portfolio
- resume
- system info
- calculator
- notes
- clock
- settings

Still not implemented from the broader roadmap:

- weather

## Current AI Agent Status

The AI agent currently supports:

- identity-driven answers based on `docs/project/*`, `docs/maivand/info.json`, and roadmap context
- recruiter/client-facing guided prompts
- opening installed apps through the OS runtime
- guided portfolio and hiring/contact flows
- note draft creation through the Notes app
- a visible desktop-shell teaser widget that can be dragged like a real widget

## Near-term Goals

The next major milestone is refinement and depth rather than just adding the first batch:

- make the AI agent even closer to Maivand's real voice
- improve guided portfolio flows and deeper app targeting
- finish the remaining planned app(s)
- keep polishing responsiveness, motion, and OS realism
